# ImagesavingusingByte-

package models;

import io.ebean.Finder;
import io.ebean.Model;
import javax.persistence.Entity;
import javax.persistence.Id;
import javax.persistence.Lob;
import javax.persistence.Table;

@Entity
@Table(name ="image")
public class Image extends Model {

    public static Finder<Integer,Image> finder = new Finder<Integer,Image>(Image.class);

    @Id
    private Integer id;
    private  String imageName;
    @Lob
    private byte[] image;


    public Integer getId() {
        return id;
    }

    public void setId(Integer id) {
        this.id = id;
    }

    public String getImageName() {
        return imageName;
    }

    public void setImageName(String imageName) {
        this.imageName = imageName;
    }

    public byte[] getImage() {
        return image;
    }

    public void setImage(byte[] image) {
        this.image = image;
    }
}


//Controller
   public  Result uploadImage() {
            JsonNode imageObj = request().body().asJson();
            String imageName = imageObj.get("imageName").asText();
            String rawImage = imageObj.get("image").asText();
            Image image = new Image();
            Logger.debug("message",image);
            image.setImageName(imageName);
            image.setImage(rawImage.getBytes());
            Image.finder.db().save(image);
            return ok(Json.toJson(image.getId()));
        }
        
        //Json param using Postman
        "imageName":"photo",
    "image":"data:image/gif;base64,"
}
